{ White has some alternatives but this is the main line after playing 8. cxd5. White wants to keep the c-file open for his rook so he exchanges knights on d5 as well. This way the white's plan is clear: Bf4 and Rc1, pressing on c7. }
9... exd5
{ In this case both recaptures @@StartBracket@@pawn and bishop@@EndBracket@@ are valid.  For coherence purposes I prefer to take with the pawn because if white delays cxd5 and plays some other developing moves like 8. Ne5 or 8. Bf4 before commiting in the center.  It is very likely that we will reach positions more alike the ones we get after taking on d5 with the pawn @@StartBracket@@for instance, after Ne5 and cxd5, ...Bxd5 is not possible because the g2-bishop is open and white can play e4!, seizing the center@@EndBracket@@.  9...Bxd5 is the common answer for black in this position, so it is possible that white gets surprised for this. }
10. Bf4
{ The most logical way to continue the game, white is aiming for c7 so black must prepare to play ...c5 and play with hanging pawns. Also leaving the c1-square for the rook. }
10... Nd7
{ More precise than the direct ...c5. There is no need to push the c-pawn until it is attacked, so black first finishes his development.  The knight allows the a rook to join the action, reinforces the c5-push and even can be located either on f6 @@StartBracket@@aiming for e4@@EndBracket@@ or b6 @@StartBracket@@supporting the center and queenside@@EndBracket@@. }
11. Rc1
{ Placing another piece on his best square. Now the c7-pawn is really in danger. }
11... c5
{ Only move, but a good one. Black is ready to react on the center with his hanging pawns. }
12. dxc5
{ This is the most played move in this position, although it has been reach only on a few occasions. This is the main reaction from white in this kind of positions, fighting against the hanging pawns. }
12... bxc5
{ Black should prefer hanging pawns over IQP positions. Black is ready to place his rooks on the c-d-e-files depending on how white plays.  The knight can go to b6 bolstering the d5-pawn and the dark squared bishop can be placed on f6 hitting b2 or try to exchange it on d6. }
