14. f4 Nxd2 15. Qxd2 dxc4
{ The black pieces are slightly more active. The queen is already on the attack, the bishop on b7 is on an opened diagonal and we can continue with ...Rf6 or ...Nf6-e4. The position is balanced, but I think black's position is easier to play. }
