{ Black can transfer his pieces to the kingside and start the assault on the enemy king. }
15. Qa1 Raf8 16. Ne5 { Finally white can play this move. } 16... Rh6 17. a4 a5
{ Taking care of the queenside expansion. } 18. Nxd7
{ This exchange removes the black queen from the attack for now. It also erases black's possibilities of playing ...Bxe5 followed by ...Ndc5 with a very good position for black. }
18... Qxd7 19. Ba3 c6
{ The dark squared bishop will be removed, so the c6-pawn has to be protected with the other bishop. }
20. Bxd6 Qxd6
{ Black will replace the bishop on d7, the queen can block on b4 any action white can think of in the queenside and reposition his rooks. }
