{ This check provokes ...c6. The downside of this move is that it blocks the bishop on b7, which loses control over the e4-square. So white can open the center with a timely e3-e4.  On the upside, black no longer needs to spend a tempo on ...a6 because the c6-pawn performs the same role of preventing Nb5. }
