{ We play short castling hoping that white transposes to the main line. In fact, white has nothing better than 12. O-O. }
12. Qc2 { An alternative to  12.O-O  . } 12... h6
{ Protecting the pawn and stopping Bg5. Now white has lost his main plan in this position. }
13. O-O { I cannot find any other move that makes sense. } 13... Nd7
{ Black has just achieved the same position as in the main line but without the Bg5 headache.  The position is equal according to the engine but black's plan looks simpler.  Black can place his knight on d5 via f6 or play with the ...c6-c5 break. His rooks will move to the central files while the queen can seat on c7. }
