{ Good time to take on c4 after white's bishop has been developed. } 13. e4
{ It is not a good move. } 13... c3 { One of the pawns is falling. } 14. Bxc3
{ After  14.Qxc3  Bxe4  black is just a pawn up in a better position. } 14...
Bxa3 15. Qa4 Bd6
{ Going back to safety. If black can play ...e6-e5 black will reach a very good position with an extra pawn and a blocked center. }
16. e5 Bb4
{ This is the only move that does not lose a piece, but the exclamation mark is for the maneuver ...Bd6-Bb4 since we get a better position than if we play ...Bb4 directly. White's center is now fixed and it is harder to defend. }
17. Bxb4 { White has nothing better. } 17... Qxb4+ 18. Qxb4 axb4 19. Kd2
{ This move is not an improvement. } 19... Ke7
{ Black now can fight to keep his extra pawn. } *

