{ Black's plan is the same as in the main line with  5.Bd3  :  ...d5-Bd6-Nbd7-a6 and O-O in one order or the other. }
6. O-O Bd6
{ We can play ...Bd6 since white has choose to play very passively and white has no way to punish us because of it. }
7. Nc3 a6
{ There is no need to worry too much in this opening since white just wants to play a safe game.  If black develops as in the 5.Bd3 line we will get a good position without any troubles. White has less control of the e4-square.  Moreover, white cannot play useful moves like Ne2-Ng3 or Qe2 because the bishop is on the way without any reward to compensate for it. }
