6... Ne4 7. Qc2 { If  7.Qb3  we transpose to a known position with  ...Qe7  . }
7... O-O 8. Bd3 f5 { Supporting the e4-knight and controlling the center. } 9.
O-O-O { The king will be too exposed. } 9... Bxc3 10. bxc3 Qe7 11. Kb2
{ White has to stop ...Qa3+. } 11... Nc6
{ Black is faster on the queenside and in the center of the board. Black wants to put the knight on a5 to pressure the c4-pawn. }
