11... Bxf4 { And we happily accept it. } 12. exf4 Bxf3
{ And we take on f3 to ruin white's pawn structure. } 13. gxf3 Nf6
{ And after this move white has no way of amend his pawns. } 14. Bb5+ Kf7
{ Losing the right to castle, but the king is safe on f7. } 15. Bc6 Rb8
{ White's structure is dreadful. The position is still equal according to computer, but honestly I do not understand it.  The c6-bishop is restricting black's pieces somehow, but it does not feel enough to compensate the fact that white has 5 @@StartBracket@@five!@@EndBracket@@ weak pawns and even more holes.  White has to play for a quick d5, probably after O-O-O but still... }
