c5 11. O-O Qc7 { We play this move first to stop Bf4. } 12. Qe2
{ Up to this point white always plays this moves. Black can continue with: }
12... Rd8 { Aiming at d4. } 13. Re1 Nd7 { Developing the last minor piece. }
14. Bd2 Rac8
{ With an equal position, with chances for both players. This line is not very incisive and black can develop without any trouble. }
