{ Moves like Na2 or Nb1 are a waste of time. The knight would be very limited, and white achieves nothing maintaining the knight passivately. }
17... Bxc3 18. bxc3 Nc6 { The rook must be saved. } 19. Bf3 Rac8
{ Removing the rook from the diagonal. ...f7-f5 is a threat, putting away the white queen from the action. }
20. Rfb1 { It's another possibility, but white needs to be precise. } 20... f5
21. Qc2 Rc7 { The game could continue: } 22. Rb2 a5 23. Bxc6
{ It seems dangerous because of white's castling, but otherwise white will end up crushed on the queenside. }
23... Qxc6 24. Rxa5 Rf6 25. e4 { An only move again. } 25... fxe4 26. Raxb5
{ With equality. } *

