19. Rb1 Qe6 { Hitting the loose rook. Black is safe. } 20. Rh5
{ The engine prefers this, but feels unnatural to me. } 20... g6 21. Rh4 Bg7
22. Rc4 Rfe8
{ Black has an isolated pawn on c5, but we can easily defend it with the bishop. White has also some weak pawns on e2 @@StartBracket@@it can be easily protected with e2-e3@@EndBracket@@ and a2. }
