{ This leads to very complex positions that have practically never been played. Both players must be very precise in order not to get worse. }
14. Ne2
{ Force a sequence of unique moves for both sides.  There is no need to study this. }
14... c5
{ To show the complexity of this line I will place an exclamation mark to all the only move in this line. Even to the 'easy' ones. }
15. e5 Bxg2 16. exf6 Bxf1 17. fxg7 Re8 18. Nh6+ Kxg7 19. Nxd4 Bh3 20. Ndf5+ Kg6
21. Qc2 Ne6 22. Nd6+ f5 23. Nhxf5 Nxf4 24. gxf4 Rf8
