12. e4 dxc4 { We get the better pawn structure. } 13. Qxc4 b5 14. Qe2 Qc7
{ Our pawn structure is sounder. We will push forward the queenside and place a rook on d8.The e5-pawn is hanging, but we do not need to take it. It could be bad in some cases since we are wasting time on a pawn that is already doomed.  The only way to defend it is playing f2-f4. In that case, the diagonal a7-g1 would be weak. }
