13... b5 14. Qb3 { White must protect the weakness on b4. } 14... a5
{ ...Nxe5 can also be considered, but with this move white is forced to play very precisely. ...axb4 is very strong. }
15. e4 { Only move. } 15... d4
{ As always in these positions, when white plays e4 we answer ...d4. } 16. Ne2
d3 { Stopping Nd4 for the moment. The knight on d4 is fine if it is stable. }
17. Qxd3 { Only move. } 17... Nxe5 18. Qb3
{ Exchanging queens is not an option for white. Our pieces are much better developed. }
18... Qc7 19. bxa5 Rfe8
{ Coming to a balanced position. Black's moves seem easier to play. White must cross a minefield to get to an even position. }
