{ It is always hard to face a novelty over the board. According to engine it is an inaccuracy, but nothing too bad is happening.   15...Bxb2  Is the course suggestion. }
16. Nd6 Ba6 17. Qxd5
{ An strange sacrifice, it was not needed.   17.Re1  Is just natural and also good.  17...Bxb2  18.Bxd5  Nf6!  19.Bxf7+  Rxf7  20.Qb3  Bxa1  21.Qxf7+  Kh8  22.Rxa1⩲  With white's pieces being slightly better placed in the likely ensuing ending. }
17... Bxf1 18. Kxf1 Rb8 19. Rd1
{ 19.Rc1⩲  Keeps the pressure. Black cannot contest the c-file due to the knight on d6. Nxf7 is looming and black has to be precise to equalize. }
19... Nc5 20. Nxf7 { Otherwise black is freeing himself. } 20... Rxf7 21. b4
Qxd5 22. Bxd5 Rd8
{ Black secures the 7th rank after white gets back his material. } 23. bxc5
bxc5 24. Be3
{ A difficult mistake to explain. White just throws the game.   24.Bxf7+  Kxf7  25.Rc1=  With an equal endgame. }
24... Kh8
{ The rook on d1 is undefended so white will not get back his material. Black is an exchange up and he is completely winning. }
