1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b6 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. c4 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Be7 7. Nc3 c6 8. O-O
d5 9. Ne5 O-O 10. Bf4 Nbd7 11. Qa4 Nxe5 12. Bxe5
{ A move later and with a very different move order we have reached a position of the course. }
12... a6
{ Differing from the course on the first move. Tiviakov follows the ...a6-b5 plan without removing the f6-knight first but this is not a major change since the main plans are the same.   The course recommendation was  12...Nd7  @@StartBracket@@we reached this position on move  11.  @@EndBracket@@ }
13. Qb3 b5 14. cxd5 cxd5 15. Rfc1 Qa5
{ A mistake. It traps the queen and allows the Bc7! trick. This is why ...Nd7 before was an improvement as moves like ...Qb6 would be possible since the queen on b6 would be protected and Na4 would be eliminated as an option for white.   15...Nd7?!  After white has placed a rook on the c-file, this move is no longer good.  16.Bc7⩲  With Nxd5 being the key move.   15...Ng4  Black needs to play something like this.  16.Bf4  Qb6= }
16. Rc2
{ Missing the chance. Now black is comfortable again.   16.Nxb5!  The missed tactic for both players.  16...Qxb5  17.Qxb5  axb5  18.Rc7±  Regaining the piece with an extra pawn. White will also control the open c-file and the 7th rank, leaving a highway for his queenside pawns. }
16... Rfc8 { Going to the key c-file. } 17. Rac1 Nd7 18. Bf4 Rc4
{ Taking advantage of the stronghold on c4. } 19. Bd2
{ Missing the thread. After retreating the queen to a safer square black would have two major threats: the d4-pawn and ...Rb4 followed by a discovered attack.   19.Nb1=  After this move the game remains equal. }
19... Qd8 { Protecting the e7-bishop, enabling both threats. } 20. e3
{ There is no good choice for white. White tried to save the d4-pawn but it has its cost. }
20... Rb4 21. Nxd5 { Finding a practical chance. } 21... Rxb3 22. Nxe7+ Qxe7
23. Bxb7 Rb8 24. Bg2 Rb4
{ Black got a queen for a pawn and a bishop although the rook on b4 is trapped, so the real balance is a queen for a rook and a pawn. Still a huge advantage for black. The game ended somehow in a draw as white found a fortress in a queen vs rook endgame. }
